&gt; have no problem with him. IT takes a big 
&gt; person to change and admit they were wrong, 
&gt; and I don't think Shiron is ready for that 
&gt; now and probably ever will be. He is to 
&gt; hyped up on his power trip. The power trip 
&gt; he gets off of everyone that buys from him. 

&gt; I know that the people of Norrath will do 
&gt; the right thing. I have faith that the 
&gt; people of Norrath will not stand for this 
&gt; type of behavior from anyone. Any comments? 
&gt; Do you agree? Disagree? I welcome 
&gt; intelligent comments. I welcome valid 
&gt; flames. I do not welcome ignorant comments 
&gt; or flames. Long live Tunare! Long live 
&gt; Mithanial Marr! Long live the good people of 
&gt; Norrath! Long live the Sacred Haven! 

&gt; p.s. 

&gt; This is addressed to Kynneth, a member of 
&gt; the Guardians of Light. Kynneth, about 4 
&gt; paragraphs above I mentioned that one 
&gt; advantage I have was to not tell my true 
&gt; smithing skill to anyone I do not trust. 
&gt; Despite any slight differences we had in the 
&gt; past, I trust you. So you know my true 
&gt; ability, if you still remember what I told 
&gt; you. If Shiron or another comes to you and 
&gt; asks what my ability is, I trust you. That 
&gt; is all I have to say. 
